bug.author: BaiGang
bug.summary: Broken link to doc in extras.
bug.description: In the <denchmark-link:https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/tf/nn/nce_loss>doc on nec_loss</denchmark-link> , the target doc of the "Candidate Sampling Algorithms Reference ", of which the url is <denchmark-link:https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/extras/candidate_sampling.pdf>https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/extras/candidate_sampling.pdf</denchmark-link> , is missing and gives just a 404 error.

comments.comment: I find the doc in <denchmark-link:https://www.tensorflow.org/extras/candidate_sampling.pdf>https://www.tensorflow.org/extras/candidate_sampling.pdf</denchmark-link> . So I believe it's due to an improperly specified URL path.

I put in a redirect for this and corrected the API docstrings internally, but it has to propagate out to the site. Still, you should get redirected now (you may have to reload your browser if the 404 is cached)
